## Scoring Rubric (Quick Reference)

| Score | Meaning | Criteria |
|-------|---------|----------|
| 0 | Absent | Nothing detected for this pillar |
| 1-3 | Minimal | Some tooling exists but incomplete or misconfigured |
| 4-6 | Moderate | Core tooling in place, gaps in coverage or hardening |
| 7-8 | Strong | Comprehensive tooling, well-configured, few gaps |
| 9-10 | Exemplary | Best-in-class, optimised for speed, security, and reliability |

See `references/cicd-best-practices.md` for detailed per-pillar scoring criteria.

