## Gap-to-Action Mapping

| Gap Detected | Recommendation | Action |
|---|---|---|
| No CI/CD pipeline at all | Set up GitHub Actions with build, test, and lint workflows | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No caching configured | Add dependency and build caching to reduce build times | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No concurrency controls | Add concurrency groups to cancel redundant workflow runs | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No path filters | Add path-based triggers to avoid unnecessary builds | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No integration/E2E tests in CI | Add service containers and E2E test jobs | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No static analysis in CI | Add linting, type checking, and code scanning to workflows | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No security scanning | Add CodeQL, dependency scanning, and secrets detection | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| Actions not SHA-pinned | Pin all third-party actions to commit SHAs | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| Overly permissive permissions | Add `permissions: {}` at workflow level, scope per-job | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No CODEOWNERS | Create CODEOWNERS file with meaningful ownership | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No PR template | Create PR template with checklist and context sections | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No AI-assisted review | Evaluate and configure AI code review tooling | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No test result reporting | Add test reporter for PR annotations and check run summaries | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No selective execution | Add `dorny/paths-filter` to run only affected checks per changed files | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| Full git clone in CI | Add `fetch-depth: 1` to checkout steps for faster clones | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| `fail-fast: true` on matrix | Set `fail-fast: false` for comprehensive test reporting across all matrix jobs | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No PR annotations from linters | Configure linter output format for GitHub annotations (`--format github`, `reviewdog`) | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No flaky test management | Add retry/quarantine strategy for flaky tests | `Task(platform-engineer)` |
| No branch protection | Enable required status checks and review approvals | Manual: configure branch protection in GitHub settings |
| No pre-commit hooks for quality | Set up pre-commit hooks for local quality gates | `Skill(setting-up-pre-commit)` |
| No justfile for CI commands | Create justfile with standardised CI-compatible recipes | `Skill(writing-justfiles)` |
| Multiple foundation gaps | Run full foundations setup | `/setup` |
| CI/CD pipeline quality gaps (caching, hardening, security, agentic review) | Run dedicated CI/CD pipeline review for detailed assessment | `/cicd-review` |

### Generating Recommendations

For each gap found during Phases 4-9, emit a recommendation block:

```markdown
### [Priority]: [Gap Title]

**Current state:** [What was detected or not detected]
**Target state:** [What best practice looks like]
**Action:** `Task(platform-engineer)` with description of what to implement
**Impact:** [Which pillar(s) this improves and by how much]
```

Group recommendations by priority:

1. **Critical** — Build or Security pillar gaps below 4. These affect deployment confidence and supply chain safety.
2. **Important** — Gaps that reduce pipeline efficiency or coverage but don't block deployments.
3. **Nice-to-Have** — Improvements that enhance developer experience or add defence-in-depth.

